<!-- please translate the heading "Examples" into ady -->
* <code><nowiki>{{lang-ab|Foo}}</nowiki></code> → {{lang-ab|Foo}}
* <code><nowiki>{{lang-ab|Foo|Buzz}}</nowiki></code> → {{lang-ab|Foo|Buzz}}
* <code><nowiki>{{lang-ab|Foo|gloss=Buzz}}</nowiki></code> → {{lang-ab|Foo|gloss=Buzz}}
* <code><nowiki>{{lang-ab|Foo|gloss=Buzz|</nowiki><u>name=no</u>}}</code> → {{lang-ab|Foo|gloss=Buzz|name=no}}
* <code><nowiki>{{lang-ab|Foo|</nowiki><u>name=no</u>}}</code> → {{lang-ab|Foo|name=no}}
* <code><nowiki>{{lang-ab|Foo|</nowiki><u>link=no</u>}}</code> → {{lang-ab|Foo|link=no}}

Other combinations are also possible. Underlined portions must be used verbatim (cannot change "no" to something else). Note that the final form using "name=no" is still useful because it wraps the text "{{lang-ab|Foo|name=no}}" in a <code><nowiki><span lang="ab"></nowiki></code> element.

